# Convert image to pytorch tensor 
SQUEEZENET_MEAN = np.array([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], dtype=np.float32)
SQUEEZENET_STD = np.array([0.229, 0.224, 0.225], dtype=np.float32)
def preprocess(img, size=224):
    transform = transforms.Compose([
        transforms.Resize(size),
        transforms.ToTensor(),
        transforms.Normalize(mean=SQUEEZENET_MEAN.tolist(),
                    std=SQUEEZENET_STD.tolist()),
    ])
    return transform(img)

# Load ImageNet dataset
img_path = '.\\images\\'

def extract_name(data_path): 
    roots = []
    folders = []
    names = []
    for root, folder, name in os.walk(data_path):
        roots.append(root) 
        folders.append(folder) 
        names.append(name)     
    return roots, folders, names

img_root,img_folder,img_name = extract_name(img_path)

label_path = img_path + img_name[0][0]
label_file = open(label_path)
label_mapping = label_file.readlines()
for i in range(len(label_mapping)):
    label_mapping[i] = label_mapping[i][0:9]

data_list = []
image_list = []
label_list = []
for i in range(len(img_root)):
    img_root[i] = img_root[i] + '\\*.JPEG'
    classID = img_folder[0][i-1]
    label = label_mapping.index(classID)
    for filename in glob.glob(img_root[i]):
        img = Image.open(filename)
        data = img.resize((224,224))
        data_list.append(data)
        img_pro = preprocess(data)
        image_list.append(img_pro)
        label_list.append(label)

#convert image and label list to tensor
task_list = [ torch.autograd.Variable(item.unsqueeze(0)) for item in image_list]
task_list = torch.cat(task_list, dim = 0)
task_label = np.asarray(label_list)
task_label = torch.tensor(task_label).long().view(-1)
In [4]:
class Dataset(Dataset):
    def __init__(self, input, label):
        super(Dataset).__init__()
        self.input = input
        self.label = label

    def __getitem__(self, item):
        return self.input[item,:,:,:], self.label[item]

    def __len__(self):
        return self.input.shape[0]

task_iter = DataLoader(Dataset(torch.tensor(task_list).float(), task_label.long()),batch_size=15,shuffle=False)

In [6]:
# Use cross entropy to compute saliency maps
criterion = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss()

def saliency_map(inp_img, inp_lb, model, loss_func = criterion):    
    model.eval()
    
    # Wrap the input tensors in Variables
    X = torch.autograd.Variable(inp_img, requires_grad=True)
    y = torch.autograd.Variable(inp_lb)
    saliency = None
     
    # forward pass
    preds = model(X)

    loss = loss_func(preds, y)
    loss.backward()
    
    grads = X.grad
    grads = grads.abs()
    
    # get max abs from all 3 channels
    saliency, _ = torch.max(grads, dim=1)
    
    return saliency
In [7]:
if torch.cuda.is_available():
    pretrained_model.cuda()
    task_list = task_list.cuda()
    task_label = task_label.cuda()

N = task_list.shape[0]
saliency_res = np.ones((N,224,224))

def postprocess(img):
    img = (img - img.min()) / (img.max() - img.min()) * 255
    img = img.astype(np.uint8)

    return img

saliency_res = saliency_map(task_list, task_label, pretrained_model).cpu().numpy()

for i in range(N):
    plt.subplot(10, N/5 , 6 * (i // 3) + i%3 + 1)
    plt.imshow(data_list[i])
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.subplot(10, N/5, 6 * (i// 3) + i%3 + 4)
    plt.imshow(postprocess(saliency_res[i]), cmap=plt.cm.hot)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.gcf().set_size_inches(10, 30)
    plt.suptitle("Saliency result for images Before style transfer",fontsize=20,x=0.5,y=0.9,)
plt.show()

# Load images after style transfer
new_img_path = '.\\transfer_images\\'

new_img_root,new_img_folder,new_img_name = extract_name(new_img_path)

new_label_path = new_img_path + new_img_name[0][0]
new_label_file = open(new_label_path)
new_label_mapping = new_label_file.readlines()
for i in range(len(new_label_mapping)):
    new_label_mapping[i] = new_label_mapping[i][0:9]

new_data_list = []
new_image_list = []
new_label_list = []
for i in range(len(new_img_root)):
    new_img_root[i] = new_img_root[i] + '\\*.PNG'
    new_classID = new_img_folder[0][i-1]
    new_label = new_label_mapping.index(new_classID)
    for filename in glob.glob(new_img_root[i]):
        new_img = Image.open(filename).convert('RGB')
        new_data = new_img.resize((224,224))
        new_data_list.append(new_data)
        new_img_pro = preprocess(new_data)
        new_image_list.append(new_img_pro)
        new_label_list.append(new_label)

#convert image and label list to tensor
new_task_list = [ torch.autograd.Variable(item.unsqueeze(0)) for item in new_image_list]

new_task_label = np.asarray(new_label_list)
